## Design Specifications
* Coded in Swift 5.3
* Must use MVVM architecture (Models, ViewModels and Views are separated)
* UI components: 3 x UITableView to display a list of accounts
    * Each row contains information about account: balance and name
    * Clicking on each row should open a modal with 2 buttons: “Withdraw” and “Deposit”
    * Upon tapping withdraw button, the textfield below the tableview shows a field for entering withdrawal amount. Upon tapping deposit button (in this case it is a deposit) text field above shows a field to enter deposit amount
    * Clicking “Withdraw” should subtract that amount from current balance and click “Deposit” should add that amount to current balance
* Must have one class for each layer of the MVVM architecture
* Use Cocoa Pods to manage dependencies (If you don’t know Cocoa pods, check out this link: http://blog.krzyzanowskim.com/2015/08/04/using-cocoapods-for-ios-development) 
* Unit test cases using UI testing (no need to implement unit tests for models and viewModels)